## Important Conventions

### Code Style
- Follow existing fairseq2 code style (Black formatting, type hints)
- Use descriptive variable names matching the domain
- Prefer composition over inheritance where fairseq2 does
- Use dataclasses for configuration (match recipe patterns)

### Naming Patterns in fairseq2
- `*Builder`: Factory classes for constructing objects
- `*Config`: Configuration dataclasses
- `*Factory`: Protocols or abstract classes for object creation
- `create_*`: Factory functions
- `setup_*`: Initialization functions with side effects
- `*Hub`: Registry pattern for models, datasets, tokenizers

